        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Agreement to accept Castleman's lot in the "Common Field" of St. Genevieve, Mo., in exchange for debt on Texas land.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>Whereas <persName>Sylvanus Castleman</persName> has this day given a power of 
attorney to <persName>Henry Elliott</persName> of <placeName>St Genivieve Missouri</placeName> to sell a lot of land
in the common field of said Town&#8212;Now I do hereby agree to take
the said lot of ground as a full compensation for surveying said
<placeName><persName>castleman</persName>s land</placeName> in <placeName>Austin's Colony</placeName> in the <placeName>Province of Texas</placeName> and
for getting the title to said land, hereby giving him a receipt in
full for all fees on said land&#8212;provided that if the title to said land
be defective or incumbered this contract is to be void</p>

<p><placeName>Austin's Colony</placeName> <date when="1822-03-01">March 1. 1822</date></p>

<p><persName>Stephen F. Austin </persName>   [Rubric]</p>

        </div1>
